				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Well, memory mapped registers are traditionally all uppercase (e.g. PPUMASK, PPUSTATUS, PPUDATA). The official Atari 2600 manuals also have registers names in uppercase (e.g. RESP1, COLUPF, GRP0). So even though I don't use the exact same register names as the NesDev Wiki does, mine are still uppercase.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

